        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "## Atlas Platform — Service Availability\n\n**Prometheus** (green = UP): Scraping all targets and evaluating alert rules. Alert rules loaded from `prometheus/alert-rules.yml`.\n\n**atlas-portal** (green = UP): Instrumented with `prom-client`. Exposes `/metrics` with Node.js process metrics.\n\n**orion-api** (green = UP): Instrumented with `prometheus-fastapi-instrumentator`. Exposes `/metrics` with per-route HTTP request duration histograms.\n\n**airflow (probe)** (green = UP): Monitored via `blackbox-exporter` HTTP probe to `http://airflow:8080/health`. `probe_success=1` means HTTP 2xx was received.\n\n**Firing Alerts** (green = None, red = count): Shows the number of alerts currently in FIRING state. Three rules are defined — AtlasPortalDown, OrionApiDown, AirflowHealthDown — each fires after the target is down for 1 minute. Alerts are forwarded to Alertmanager → webhook (configured via `ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL` in `.env`).\n\n**Test an alert:** `docker compose stop portal` → wait 60–90 s → check http://localhost:9090/alerts and http://localhost:9093 → recover with `docker compose start portal`.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
